specifyClockToDataSpacing(25.10)              specifyClockToDataSpacing(25.10)

Name
       specifyClockToDataSpacing

Syntax
        specifyClockToDataSpacing

       [-help]

       {{-cell  <clockCell> {[-x <leftRightSpacing> ] [-y <topBottomSpacing> |
       -reset }

       You can use  specifyClockToDataSpacing  to  specify  the  clock-to-data
       spacing.  Placement honors this spacing rule to check and legalize it.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each specifyClockToDataSpacing parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specifyClockToDataSpacing

       -cell <clockCell>
              Specifies  the clock cell.

       -reset Clears all clock-to-data spacing rules.

       -x<leftRightSpacing>
              Specifies the spacing on both left/right sides.

       -y<topBottomSpacing>>
              Specifies the spacing on both top/bottom sides.

